broadsoft.description: This document contains the management information that is common to all elements in a Broadworks system.

msPortsInUse.name: msPortsInUse
msPortsInUse.description: Total numbers of ports currently in use

msConfCurrentPortsInUse.name: msConfCurrentPortsInUse
msConfCurrentPortsInUse.description: Number of conferencing ports currently in use

msConfTotalDuration.name: msConfTotalDuration
msConfTotalDuration.description: Total duration of all conferences (in seconds)

msIvrFreeAudioMemory.name: msIvrFreeAudioMemory
msIvrFreeAudioMemory.description: Memory available for audio files (in bytes)

msIvrAudioMemoryInUse.name: msIvrAudioMemoryInUse
msIvrAudioMemoryInUse.description: Audio memory currently in use (in bytes)

msIvrCurrentPortsInUse.name: msIvrCurrentPortsInUse
msIvrCurrentPortsInUse.description: Number of IVR ports currently in use

msIvrTotalDuration.name: msIvrTotalDuration
msIvrTotalDuration.description: Total duration of all IVR sessions (in seconds)

msIvrTotalRecordingDuration.name: msIvrTotalRecordingDuration
msIvrTotalRecordingDuration.description: Total duration of recorded voice messages (in seconds)

msIvrEmptyRecordings.name: msIvrEmptyRecordings
msIvrEmptyRecordings.description: Number of recordings that failed due to too few RTP packets received. This may be due to silence suppression at the remote RTP device, or the network dropping packets.

msRtpSessionsInUse.name: msRtpSessionsInUse
msRtpSessionsInUse.description: Total number of active RTP sessions

msRtcpSenderReports.name: msRtcpSenderReports
msRtcpSenderReports.description: Number of RTCP sender reports received

msRtpPacketsExpected.name: msRtpPacketsExpected
msRtpPacketsExpected.description: Total number of packets that were expected

msRtpOutOfOrder.name: msRtpOutOfOrder
msRtpOutOfOrder.description: Number of RTP packets that were received out of order

msRtpBadPayload.name: msRtpBadPayload
msRtpBadPayload.description: Number of packets received which had a bad payload type

msRtpSsrc.name: msRtpSsrc
msRtpSsrc.description: Number of packets received that had an invalid SSRC

msRtpReceivedPacketJitter.name: msRtpReceivedPacketJitter
msRtpReceivedPacketJitter.description: Total jitter of packets received by this node

msRtpCumulativePacketsLost.name: msRtpCumulativePacketsLost
msRtpCumulativePacketsLost.description: Cumulative count of packets sent by this node but reported lost by remote nodes

msRtpFramesSkipped.name: msRtpFramesSkipped
msRtpFramesSkipped.description: Number of frames that were skipped because CPU is overloaded (one frame = 1 packet per RTP session)

msRtpTransmitJitter.name: msRtpTransmitJitter
msRtpTransmitJitter.description: Jitter of packets transmitted by this node, as measured by remote nodes

msPrimaryEmailSent.name: msPrimaryEmailSent
msPrimaryEmailSent.description: Number of messages sent to primary SMTP server

msPrimarySmtpErrors.name: msPrimarySmtpErrors
msPrimarySmtpErrors.description: Number of errors that occured to primary SMTP server

msSecondaryEmailSent.name: msSecondaryEmailSent
msSecondaryEmailSent.description: Number of e-mails sent to secondary SMTP server

msSecondarySmtpErrors.name: msSecondarySmtpErrors
msSecondarySmtpErrors.description: Number of errors that occured to secondary SMTP server

msAlarmsCount.name: msAlarmsCount
msAlarmsCount.description: Number of alarms sent (i.e., SNMP Traps)

msSoftwareErrorsCount.name: msSoftwareErrorsCount
msSoftwareErrorsCount.description: Number of software errors that were reported

msACLViolationCount.name: msACLViolationCount
msACLViolationCount.description: Number of sip messages received from unauthorized host

msMaxCapacityInPorts.name: msMaxCapacityInPorts
msMaxCapacityInPorts.description: The maximum number of 'G.711 ports' the MS is capable of handling

msNumLicensedPorts.name: msNumLicensedPorts
msNumLicensedPorts.description: The maximum number of licensed ports the MS is authorized to use according to its license file.

msSipStatsInviteIns.name: msSipStatsInviteIns
msSipStatsInviteIns.description: Number of INVITE requests received by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsAckIns.name: msSipStatsAckIns
msSipStatsAckIns.description: Number of ACK requests received by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsByeIns.name: msSipStatsByeIns
msSipStatsByeIns.description: Number of BYE requests received by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsByeOuts.name: msSipStatsByeOuts
msSipStatsByeOuts.description: Number of BYE requests sent by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsInfoIns.name: msSipStatsInfoIns
msSipStatsInfoIns.description: Number of INFO requests received by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsInfoOuts.name: msSipStatsInfoOuts
msSipStatsInfoOuts.description: Number of INFO requests sent by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsOthersIns.name: msSipStatsOthersIns
msSipStatsOthersIns.description: Number of UNKNOWN requests received by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsOthersOuts.name: msSipStatsOthersOuts
msSipStatsOthersOuts.description: Number of UNKNOWN requests sent by the MediaServer.

msSipStatsResponsesIns.name: msSipStatsResponsesIns
msSipStatsResponsesIns.description: Number of responses received by the MediaServer, excluding retransmissions.

msSipStatsResponsesOuts.name: msSipStatsResponsesOuts
msSipStatsResponsesOuts.description: Number of responses sent by the MediaServer, excluding retransmissions.

msSipStatsInvite200OKRetransmitsOuts.name: msSipStatsInvite200OKRetransmitsOuts
msSipStatsInvite200OKRetransmitsOuts.description: Number of 200 OK to a SIP INVITE that were retransmitted by the media server to a SIP user agent.

msSipStatsRequestRetransmittedIns.name: msSipStatsRequestRetransmittedIns
msSipStatsRequestRetransmittedIns.description: Number of SIP requests retransmitted by a remote SIP user agent to the media server.

msSipStatsReferOuts.name: msSipStatsReferOuts
msSipStatsReferOuts.description: Number of SIP REFER sent by the media server.

msRedirectsCount.name: msRedirectsCount
msRedirectsCount.description: This is the total number of times SIP Redirect Response (3xx) was received from the Load Balancer/SIP Redirect Proxy in response to INVITE.

msTimeOutRouteAdvancesCount.name: msTimeOutRouteAdvancesCount
msTimeOutRouteAdvancesCount.description: This is the total number of times the initial INVITE from MS to the end point times out and a new IINVITE is sent to the next end point on the contact URI list.

msRouteAdvancesCount.name: msRouteAdvancesCount
msRouteAdvancesCount.description: This is the total number of times MS had to iterate through the contact URI list either returned in the SIP Redirect Response or configured via CLI (for ASR and TTS servers)

msMSCMLTotalRecordingDuration.name: msMSCMLTotalRecordingDuration
msMSCMLTotalRecordingDuration.description: Duration of all MSCML sessions (in seconds).

msMSCMLEmptyRecordings.name: msMSCMLEmptyRecordings
msMSCMLEmptyRecordings.description: Number of recordings that failed due to too few RTP packets received. This may be due to silence suppression at the remote RTP device, or the network dropping packets.

msFilesRetrievedFromCache.name: msFilesRetrievedFromCache
msFilesRetrievedFromCache.description: total number of files retrieved from cache

msLiveAudioRequestCount.name: msLiveAudioRequestCount
msLiveAudioRequestCount.description: total number of live audio request

msLiveAudioFailureCount.name: msLiveAudioFailureCount
msLiveAudioFailureCount.description: total number of live audio failure

msLiveAudioTotalDuration.name: msLiveAudioTotalDuration
msLiveAudioTotalDuration.description: total duration of all live audio sessions (in seconds)

msLiveAudioULawUserCount.name: msLiveAudioULawUserCount
msLiveAudioULawUserCount.description: current number of live audio sessions with ulaw codec.

msLiveAudioALawUserCount.name: msLiveAudioALawUserCount
msLiveAudioALawUserCount.description: current number of live audio sessions with alaw codec.

msLiveAudioG726UserCount.name: msLiveAudioG726UserCount
msLiveAudioG726UserCount.description: current number of live audio sessions with g726 codec.

msLiveAudioG729UserCount.name: msLiveAudioG729UserCount
msLiveAudioG729UserCount.description: current number of live audio sessions with g729 codec.

msVideoRecorded.name: msVideoRecorded
msVideoRecorded.description: This counter is incremented whenever a video stream is recorded.

msVideoPlayback.name: msVideoPlayback
msVideoPlayback.description: This counter is incremented whenever a video stream is played back.

msFaxReceived.name: msFaxReceived
msFaxReceived.description: This counter is incremented whenever an MS receives a fax on behalf of Broadworks subscriber.

msFaxReceptionFailure.name: msFaxReceptionFailure
msFaxReceptionFailure.description: This counter is incremented whenever an MS fails to receive a fax on behalf of Broadworks subscriber.

msFaxPrinted.name: msFaxPrinted
msFaxPrinted.description: This counter is incremented whenever an MS sends a fax on behalf of Broadworks subscriber.

msFaxPrintingFailure.name: msFaxPrintingFailure
msFaxPrintingFailure.description: This counter is incremented whenever an MS fails to send a fax on behalf of Broadworks subscriber.

msVoiceXMLErrorCount.name: msVoiceXMLErrorCount
msVoiceXMLErrorCount.description: The VoiceXML error count counter is incremented whenever an error occurs while downloading or running a VoiceXML script.

msVoiceXMLFilesDownloaded.name: msVoiceXMLFilesDownloaded
msVoiceXMLFilesDownloaded.description: The VoiceXML files downloaded counter is incremented whenever a VoiceXML file is downloaded. It does not include media files.

msCallControlXMLCreateCallCount.name: msCallControlXMLCreateCallCount
msCallControlXMLCreateCallCount.description: Total number of CallControlXML calls created through the createcall tag

resetAllMSCounters.name: resetAllMSCounters
resetAllMSCounters.description: When set to a value other then 0, all the counters in the system are reset to 0.

msMrcpAsrSessionsCount.name: msMrcpAsrSessionsCount
msMrcpAsrSessionsCount.description: This is the total number of completed ASR MRCP sessions.

msMrcpAsrSessionsInUse.name: msMrcpAsrSessionsInUse
msMrcpAsrSessionsInUse.description: This is the total number of currently active ASR MRCP sessions.

msMrcpTtsSessionsCount.name: msMrcpTtsSessionsCount
msMrcpTtsSessionsCount.description: This is the total number of completed TTS MRCP sessions.

msMrcpTtsSessionsInUse.name: msMrcpTtsSessionsInUse
msMrcpTtsSessionsInUse.description: This is the total number of currently active TTS MRCP sessions.

msMrcpRecognitionAttemptsCount.name: msMrcpRecognitionAttemptsCount
msMrcpRecognitionAttemptsCount.description: This is the total number of times a RECOGNIZE request is executed during MRCP sessions.

msMrcpSuccessfulRecognitionsCount.name: msMrcpSuccessfulRecognitionsCount
msMrcpSuccessfulRecognitionsCount.description: This is the total number of times a RECOGNIZE request is executed successfully during MRCP sessions.

msMrcpRequestsCount.name: msMrcpRequestsCount
msMrcpRequestsCount.description: This is the total number of MRCP requests.

msMrcpFailedRequestsCount.name: msMrcpFailedRequestsCount
msMrcpFailedRequestsCount.description: This is the total number of failed MRCP requests.

msMrcpFailedConnectionsCount.name: msMrcpFailedConnectionsCount
msMrcpFailedConnectionsCount.description: This is the total number of times TCP or TLS connection attempts failed during initiating of an MRCP session.

msMrcpKeepAliveFailuresCount.name: msMrcpKeepAliveFailuresCount
msMrcpKeepAliveFailuresCount.description: This is the total number of times GET-PARAMS command sent to ASR/TTS server fails to receive a response in a timely manner during initiating MRCP sessions.

msMrcpSpeakRequestsCount.name: msMrcpSpeakRequestsCount
msMrcpSpeakRequestsCount.description: This is the total number of times SPEAK requests sent through the control channel to the TTS server.

msMrcpSpeakRequestFailuresCount.name: msMrcpSpeakRequestFailuresCount
msMrcpSpeakRequestFailuresCount.description: This is the total number of times SPEAK request sent to TTS server fails to receive a response <<SPEAK-COMPLETE>> with the completion cause other than <<Completion-Cause:000 normal>>.

bwMSGroupFax.description: This group defines global counters for the support of fax by the media server.
